{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Exempt 2330-qualified electricians with 15+ years experience from retraining",
        "additional_details": "The 2330 has long been the UK\u2019s trusted electrotechnical qualification, with thousands of holders delivering safe, compliant work across homes and businesses. For experienced electricians \u2013 many in their 50s/60s \u2013 we feel mandatory retraining would impose unfair financial hardship, duplicate skills they\u2019ve proven through decades of practice, and risk losing valuable seasoned expertise that keeps our electrical trade safe and reliable for communities nationwide.",
        "background": "Give 'Grandfather rights' to the 2330 qualification for electricians with 15+ years\u2019 documented professional experience, ensuring they can work in core roles without requiring retraining. ",
